text.tspan: Unemployment rate in people with vs. without disability, 2023
Unemployment refers to individuals of working age (typically 15 years and over) currently unemployed but actively
seeking work. A person with a disability is defined as someone limited in the kind or amount of activities they can
do due to a long-term health problem.
